{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881631906,"sessionID":"ses_285350a29ffeB2dvpQSqmyj5D4","part":{"id":"prt_d7acb2862001sTLayjsj3jzmAT","messageID":"msg_d7acb0e0e001j7VZ2qHrfEi6KA","sessionID":"ses_285350a29ffeB2dvpQSqmyj5D4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8dc840a69ead4324b4ed458e29ed6d1b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-028 |\n8: | Module | sdk-python |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Provide a Python SDK client (`AgentRuntimeClient`) for invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router. This client enables users to:\n17: \n18: 1. Bootstrap session IDs via GET request to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint\n19: 2. Send JSON payloads to Agent Runtime workloads with session header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n20: 3. Manage client lifecycle via context manager protocol\n21: 4. Configure timeouts and connection pooling for HTTP requests\n22: \n23: This is the second public client class exported from the `agentcube` package, complementing `CodeInterpreterClient` for code interpreter sessions.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n28: \n29: ### 2.1 In Scope\n30: \n31: - `AgentRuntimeClient` class implementation with:\n32:   - Constructor accepting `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`\n33:   - Context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n34:   - `invoke(payload, timeout)` method for sending JSON payloads\n35:   - `close()` method for closing HTTP session\n36:   - Session ID bootstrapping via GET request when `session_id` not provided\n37: \n38: - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class implementation with:\n39:   - Constructor accepting `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `pool_connections`, `pool_maxsize`\n40:   - `bootstrap_session_id()` method for GET request to invocation endpoint\n41:   - `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)` method for POST request\n42:   - `close()` method for closing HTTP session\n43:   - Class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n44: \n45: - Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeClient`\n46: - Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n47: - Unit tests for both client classes\n48: \n49: ### 2.2 Out of Scope\n50: \n51: - Control plane session management (handled by `ControlPlaneClient`)\n52: - Code interpreter operations (handled by `CodeInterpreterClient`)\n53: - Retry logic or circuit breaker patterns\n54: - Async API support\n55: - Authentication token handling on data plane (Router handles JWT)\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n60: \n61: ### 3.1 新增文件\n62: \n63: | File | Description |\n64: |------|-------------|\n65: | `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` public client class |\n66: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` internal HTTP client |\n67: | `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | Unit tests for AgentRuntimeClient |\n68: \n69: ### 3.2 修改文件\n70: \n71: | File | Change |\n72: |------|--------|\n73: | `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py` | Add export of `AgentRuntimeClient` to `__all__` |\n74: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Add export of `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n75: \n76: ### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n77: \n78: | Dependency | Purpose |\n79: |------------|---------|\n80: | `requests` | HTTP client library (already in pyproject.toml) |\n81: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` for connection pooling |\n82: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` for logging |\n83: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy (not actively raised by AgentRuntimeClient) |\n84: \n85: ### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n86: \n87: | Consumer | Usage |\n88: |----------|-------|\n89: | End users | Invoke Agent Runtime workloads via SDK |\n90: | Example scripts | `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py` (optional) |\n91: | Integration tests | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` (optional extension) |\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n96: \n97: ### Alternative 1: Single unified client\n98: \n99: Combine `AgentRuntimeClient` and `CodeInterpreterClient` into a single `AgentCubeClient` with mode switching.\n100: \n101: **Rejected:** Different lifecycle semantics. CodeInterpreter requires control plane session creation/deletion; AgentRuntime only bootstraps session via data plane GET. Separate clients provide cleaner APIs.\n102: \n103: ### Alternative 2: Async-first API\n104: \n105: Implement async/await based client using `aiohttp`.\n106: \n107: **Rejected:** SDK currently uses synchronous `requests` library. Adding async would double the API surface and require new dependency. Async support can be added in future AR if needed.\n108: \n109: ### Alternative 3: Session ID passed directly to invoke\n110: \n111: Require users to call `bootstrap_session_id()` manually and pass session_id to each `invoke()`.\n112: \n113: **Rejected:** UX would be poor. Client should manage session lifecycle transparently, similar to `CodeInterpreterClient` pattern.\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ## 5. Risks\n118: \n119: | Risk | Mitigation |\n120: |------|------------|\n121: | Router URL required but not provided | Raise `ValueError` with clear message, same pattern as CodeInterpreterClient |\n122: | Session header missing in bootstrap response | Raise `ValueError` with message \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\" |\n123: | Invoke called without valid session_id | Raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` |\n124: | Connection pool exhaustion | Use configurable pool size defaults (pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10) |\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n129: \n130: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n131: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n132: - [ ] Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeClient`\n133: - [ ] Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n134: - [ ] Write unit tests for `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n135: - [ ] Write unit tests for `AgentRuntimeClient`\n136: - [ ] Verify timeout tuple semantics: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n137: - [ ] Verify session header handling: `x-agentcube-session-id`\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 7. References\n142: \n143: - python-sdk/design.md — AgentCube Python SDK design\n144: - python-sdk/spec.md — SDK specification with AgentRuntime requirements\n145: - agentcube/code_interpreter.py — Reference implementation pattern\n146: - agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py — Reference data plane client\n\n(End of file - total 146 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-028 |\n| Module | sdk-python |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nProvide a Python SDK client (`AgentRuntimeClient`) for invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router. This client enables users to:\n\n1. Bootstrap session IDs via GET request to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint\n2. Send JSON payloads to Agent Runtime workloads with session header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n3. Manage client lifecycle via context manager protocol","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775881631865,"end":1775881631904}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881631908,"sessionID":"ses_285350a29ffeB2dvpQSqmyj5D4","part":{"id":"prt_d7acb2cbd001W3xt4DlsgxN9nx","messageID":"msg_d7acb0e0e001j7VZ2qHrfEi6KA","sessionID":"ses_285350a29ffeB2dvpQSqmyj5D4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9360d73dd99f49999c5c8c7ca73181e4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient |\n8: | Module | `sdk-python` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-0 |\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: [TO BE FILLED: Define scope for SDK AgentRuntimeClient]\n16: \n17: ## Out of Scope\n18: \n19: [TO BE FILLED: Define out of scope items]\n20: \n21: ## Dependencies\n22: \n23: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n24: |------------|---------|---------|\n25: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n26: \n27: ## Deliverables\n28: \n29: | File | Description |\n30: |------|-------------|\n31: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n32: \n33: ## Acceptance Criteria\n34: \n35: - [ ] [TO BE FILLED]\n36: \n37: ## References\n38: \n39: - [TO BE FILLED: Add relevant references]\n\n(End of file - total 39 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient |\n| Module | `sdk-python` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Define scope for SDK AgentRuntimeClient]\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Define out of scope items]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/spec.md","time":{"start":1775881631869,"end":1775881631906}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881631911,"sessionID":"ses_285350a29ffeB2dvpQSqmyj5D4","part":{"id":"prt_d7acb3024001slARnqj7lHjfLK","messageID":"msg_d7acb0e0e001j7VZ2qHrfEi6KA","sessionID":"ses_285350a29ffeB2dvpQSqmyj5D4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8f9e21ab821f4be68e21ec943afcee50","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient |\n8: | Module | `sdk-python` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router (data plane). This AR focuses on the `AgentRuntimeClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` classes, enabling users to bootstrap sessions and invoke agent payloads.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### High-Level Architecture\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                          User Application                            │\n24: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n25:                                 │\n26:                                 │ AgentRuntimeClient\n27:                                 ▼\n28: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n29: │                     agentcube/agent_runtime.py                       │\n30: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n31: │  │ AgentRuntimeClient                                             │  │\n32: │  │  - session_id (bootstrapped or provided)                       │  │\n33: │  │  - router_url resolution                                       │  │\n34: │  │  - Context manager lifecycle                                   │  │\n35: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n36: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n37:                                 │\n38:                                 │ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n39:                                 ▼\n40: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n41: │             agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py            │\n42: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n43: │  │ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient                                    │  │\n44: │  │  - HTTP Session with connection pooling                        │  │\n45: │  │  - Session header: x-agentcube-session-id                      │  │\n46: │  │  - GET bootstrap_session_id()                                  │  │\n47: │  │  - POST invoke(payload)                                        │  │\n48: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n49: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n50:                                 │\n51:                                 │ HTTP Requests\n52:                                 ▼\n53: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n54: │                          Router (Data Plane)                         │\n55: │  - /v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent}/invocations/          │\n56: │  - JWT authentication (handled by Router)                           │\n57: │  - Session routing                                                  │\n58: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n59: ```\n60: \n61: ### Component Relationships\n62: \n63: | Component | Role | Dependencies |\n64: |-----------|------|--------------|\n65: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | High-level user-facing client | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`, `utils/log.py` |\n66: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Low-level HTTP client for Router | `utils/http.py`, `requests` |\n67: | `create_session` | HTTP session factory | `requests`, `HTTPAdapter` |\n68: | `get_logger` | Logging utility | `logging` |\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## Data Structures\n73: \n74: ### AgentRuntimeClient Instance Fields\n75: \n76: ```python\n77: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n78:     agent_name: str              # Target agent identifier\n79:     namespace: str               # Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n80:     timeout: int                 # Read timeout seconds (default: 120)\n81:     connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout seconds (default: 5.0)\n82:     logger: logging.Logger       # Verbose logger instance\n83:     router_url: str              # Router base URL (from arg or ROUTER_URL env)\n84:     session_id: Optional[str]    # Bootstrapped or user-provided session ID\n85:     dp_client: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient  # Data plane client instance\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Instance Fields\n89: \n90: ```python\n91: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n92:     SESSION_HEADER: str = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"  # Class constant\n93:     router_url: str              # Router base URL\n94:     namespace: str               # Kubernetes namespace\n95:     agent_name: str              # Target agent identifier\n96:     timeout: int                 # Default read timeout (120)\n97:     connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (5.0)\n98:     base_url: str                # Full invocation URL path\n99:     session: requests.Session    # HTTP session with pooling\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ### Base URL Construction\n103: \n104: ```python\n105: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n106: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ### Invoke Payload Structure\n110: \n111: ```python\n112: payload: Dict[str, Any]  # Arbitrary JSON payload for agent invocation\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ## API Contracts\n118: \n119: ### AgentRuntimeClient Public API\n120: \n121: | Method | Signature | Description |\n122: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n123: | `__init__` | `(agent_name, namespace=\"default\", router_url=None, verbose=False, session_id=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` | Initialize client |\n124: | `__enter__` | `() -> self` | Context manager entry |\n125: | `__exit__` | `(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None` | Context manager exit, calls `close()` |\n126: | `invoke` | `(payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout=None) -> Any` | Invoke agent with payload |\n127: | `close` | `() -> None` | Close HTTP session |\n128: \n129: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Public API\n130: \n131: | Method | Signature | Description |\n132: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n133: | `__init__` | `(router_url, namespace, agent_name, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0, pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` | Initialize data plane client |\n134: | `bootstrap_session_id` | `() -> str` | GET base URL to bootstrap session |\n135: | `invoke` | `(session_id, payload, timeout=None) -> Response` | POST payload to agent |\n136: | `close` | `() -> None` | Close HTTP session |\n137: \n138: ### HTTP Endpoints\n139: \n140: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n141: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n142: | `GET` | `{base_url}` | (session default) | None |\n143: | `POST` | `{base_url}` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n144: \n145: ### Timeout Behavior\n146: \n147: | Scenario | Timeout Value |\n148: |----------|---------------|\n149: | `invoke(..., timeout=None)` | `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` → `(5.0, 120)` |\n150: | `invoke(..., timeout=30)` | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` → `(5.0, 30)` |\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## Error Handling\n155: \n156: ### Exception Hierarchy\n157: \n158: ```python\n159: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n160:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n161:     pass\n162: \n163: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n164:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n165:     pass\n166: \n167: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n168:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n169:     pass\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ### Error Scenarios\n173: \n174: | Scenario | Error Type | Message |\n175: |----------|------------|---------|\n176: | Router URL missing | `ValueError` | \"Router URL must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL environment variable\" |\n177: | Missing session header in bootstrap | `ValueError` | \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\" |\n178: | Invoke without session | `ValueError` | \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\" |\n179: | HTTP request failure | `requests.exceptions.*` | Propagated from requests library |\n180: \n181: ### Error Handling Flow\n182: \n183: ```\n184: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n185: │                     invoke(payload, timeout)                         │\n186: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n187:                                 │\n188:                                 ▼\n189: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n190: │              Check session_id is not None                            │\n191: │  if not session_id: raise ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id...\")  │\n192: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n193:                                 │\n194:                                 ▼\n195: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n196: │              POST to base_url with headers                           │\n197: │  Headers: x-agentcube-session-id, Content-Type: application/json    │\n198: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n199:                                 │\n200:                                 ▼\n201: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n202: │              Return response.json()                                  │\n203: │  (or raw Response object from data plane client)                    │\n204: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ---\n208: \n209: ## Testing Strategy\n210: \n211: ### Test Categories\n212: \n213: | Category | Scope | Tools |\n214: |----------|-------|-------|\n215: | Unit Tests | Client logic, URL construction, header management | pytest, unittest.mock |\n216: | Integration Tests | HTTP interactions with mock server | pytest, responses library |\n217: | E2E Tests | Full workflow against Router | pytest, real Router instance |\n218: \n219: ### Test Scenarios\n220: \n221: #### Unit Tests\n222: \n223: | Test Case | Description |\n224: |-----------|-------------|\n225: | `test_router_url_resolution` | Verify Router URL from arg vs env var |\n226: | `test_base_url_construction` | Verify URL path `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent}/invocations/` |\n227: | `test_session_header_constant` | Verify `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n228: | `test_context_manager_enter_exit` | Verify `__enter__` returns self, `__exit__` calls `close()` |\n229: \n230: #### Integration Tests\n231: \n232: | Test Case | Description |\n233: |-----------|-------------|\n234: | `test_bootstrap_session_id_success` | Mock GET returning `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n235: | `test_bootstrap_session_id_missing_header` | Mock GET without header → raises ValueError |\n236: | `test_invoke_with_session` | Mock POST with payload and verify headers |\n237: | `test_invoke_without_session` | Call invoke before bootstrap → raises ValueError |\n238: | `test_invoke_timeout_override` | Verify timeout tuple `(5.0, 30)` when passed |\n239: \n240: #### E2E Tests\n241: \n242: | Test Case | Description |\n243: |-----------|-------------|\n244: | `test_e2e_agent_invoke` | Full workflow: bootstrap session → invoke → validate response |\n245: \n246: ### Test File Locations\n247: \n248: | File | Purpose |\n249: |------|---------|\n250: | `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` | Unit + integration tests for AgentRuntimeClient |\n251: | `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Unit + integration tests for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient |\n252: | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` | E2E test script (reference from spec) |\n253: \n254: ### Mocking Strategy\n255: \n256: ```python\n257: # Example: Mock bootstrap GET\n258: import responses\n259: import pytest\n260: \n261: @responses.activate\n262: def test_bootstrap_session_id():\n263:     responses.get(\n264:         \"http://router/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\",\n265:         headers={\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"test-session-123\"}\n266:     )\n267:     client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(...)\n268:     session_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n269:     assert session_id == \"test-session-123\"\n270: ```\n271: \n272: ---\n273: \n274: ## File Structure\n275: \n276: | Path | Role |\n277: |------|------|\n278: | `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation (NEW) |\n279: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` implementation (NEW) |\n280: | `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py` | Export `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n281: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n282: | `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` | Tests for AgentRuntimeClient (NEW) |\n283: | `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Tests for data plane client (NEW) |\n284: | `sdk-python/examples/agent_runtime_usage.py` | Usage example (NEW) |\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ## Dependencies\n289: \n290: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n291: |---------|---------|---------|\n292: | `requests` | (latest) | HTTP client for Router communication |\n293: | `PyJWT` | >=2.0.0 | JWT handling (used by other clients, included for consistency) |\n294: | `cryptography` | (latest) | Cryptographic support for JWT |\n295: | `pytest` | (dev) | Test framework |\n296: | `responses` | (dev) | HTTP mocking library |\n297: | `unittest.mock` | (stdlib) | Mocking utilities |\n298: \n299: ### pyproject.toml Dependencies\n300: \n301: ```toml\n302: dependencies = [\n303:     \"requests\",\n304:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n305:     \"cryptography\",\n306: ]\n307: \n308: [project.optional-dependencies]\n309: dev = [\n310:     \"pytest\",\n311:     \"pytest-cov\",\n312:     \"responses\",\n313: ]\n314: ```\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ## Implementation Notes\n319: \n320: ### Router URL Resolution\n321: \n322: ```python\n323: router_url = router_url or os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n324: if not router_url:\n325:     raise ValueError(\"Router URL must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL environment variable\")\n326: ```\n327: \n328: ### Session Bootstrap Flow\n329: \n330: ```python\n331: def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n332:     resp = self.session.get(self.base_url, timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout))\n333:     session_id = resp.headers.get(self.SESSION_HEADER)\n334:     if not session_id:\n335:         raise ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")\n336:     return session_id\n337: ```\n338: \n339: ### Invoke Implementation\n340: \n341: ```python\n342: def invoke(self, session_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Response:\n343:     effective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n344:     headers = {self.SESSION_HEADER: session_id, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}\n345:     resp = self.session.post(\n346:         self.base_url,\n347:         json=payload,\n348:         headers=headers,\n349:         timeout=(self.connect_timeout, effective_timeout)\n350:     )\n351:     return resp\n352: ```\n353: \n354: ### Context Manager Pattern\n355: \n356: ```python\n357: def __enter__(self):\n358:     return self\n359: \n360: def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb):\n361:     self.close()\n362:     return False  # Don't suppress exceptions\n363: ```\n364: \n365: ### Connection Pooling\n366: \n367: ```python\n368: from requests.adapters import HTTPAdapter\n369: \n370: def create_session(pool_connections: int = 10, pool_maxsize: int = 10) -> Session:\n371:     session = requests.Session()\n372:     adapter = HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=pool_connections, pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize)\n373:     session.mount(\"http://\", adapter)\n374:     session.mount(\"https://\", adapter)\n375:     return session\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### No Authorization on Data Plane\n379: \n380: The Router handles JWT authentication. The SDK does NOT set `Authorization` header on data plane requests—only the session header.\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## References\n385: \n386: - Spec: `changes/AR-028/spec.md`\n387: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md`\n388: - Tasks: `changes/AR-028/tasks.md`\n389: - Python SDK Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n390: - Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n391: - Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`\n\n(End of file - total 391 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient |\n| Module | `sdk-python` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nPython client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router (data plane). This AR focuses on the `AgentRuntimeClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` classes, enabling users to bootstrap sessions and invoke agent payloads.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","time":{"start":1775881631871,"end":1775881631908}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881631914,"sessionID":"ses_285350a29ffeB2dvpQSqmyj5D4","part":{"id":"prt_d7acb3475001lAY2jmSwfouEp6","messageID":"msg_d7acb0e0e001j7VZ2qHrfEi6KA","sessionID":"ses_285350a29ffeB2dvpQSqmyj5D4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-204ed10806e04dcc813e246a9395d0ec","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient |\n8: | Module | `sdk-python` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Implementation (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__` with router_url, namespace, agent_name, timeout, connect_timeout\n20:   - Purpose: Initialize HTTP client for Router data plane communication\n21:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n22:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestDataPlaneClientInit -v`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Implement `SESSION_HEADER` class constant `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n25:   - Purpose: Define session header name as class-level constant\n26:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n27:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient; print(AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER)\"`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3**: Implement base_url construction via `urljoin`\n30:   - Purpose: Build base_url as `/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n31:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n32:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestBaseURLConstruction -v`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T1.4**: Implement HTTP session with connection pooling (pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)\n35:   - Purpose: Create requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling\n36:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n37:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestConnectionPooling -v`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T1.5**: Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` method\n40:   - Purpose: GET base_url to bootstrap session, extract session_id from `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n41:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n42:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestBootstrapSessionID -v`\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T1.6**: Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` missing header handling\n45:   - Purpose: Raise ValueError when `x-agentcube-session-id` header missing in response\n46:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n47:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestBootstrapSessionID::test_bootstrap_missing_header -v`\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T1.7**: Implement `invoke()` method with session_id and payload parameters\n50:   - Purpose: POST to base_url with json=payload and session header\n51:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n52:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestInvoke -v`\n53: \n54: - [ ] **T1.8**: Implement `invoke()` headers with `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`\n55:   - Purpose: Set both session header and Content-Type on POST requests\n56:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n57:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestInvokeHeaders -v`\n58: \n59: - [ ] **T1.9**: Implement `invoke()` timeout override logic\n60:   - Purpose: Use passed timeout value or fall back to self.timeout\n61:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n62:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestInvokeTimeout -v`\n63: \n64: - [ ] **T1.10**: Implement `close()` method\n65:   - Purpose: Close the HTTP session connection pool\n66:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n67:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestClose -v`\n68: \n69: ### Phase 2: AgentRuntimeClient Implementation (ST-2)\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.1**: Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` with agent_name, namespace, router_url, verbose, session_id, timeout, connect_timeout\n72:   - Purpose: Initialize high-level client with all configuration parameters\n73:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n74:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestAgentRuntimeClientInit -v`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement Router URL required validation\n77:   - Purpose: Raise ValueError if router_url not provided via arg and ROUTER_URL env var\n78:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n79:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestRouterURLRequired -v`\n80: \n81: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `_resolve_router_url()` helper\n82:   - Purpose: Resolve router_url from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n83:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n84:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestRouterURLResolution -v`\n85: \n86: - [ ] **T2.4**: Implement session reuse logic when session_id provided\n87:   - Purpose: Skip bootstrap_session_id call when session_id argument is provided\n88:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n89:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestSessionReuse -v`\n90: \n91: - [ ] **T2.5**: Implement session bootstrap via AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n92:   - Purpose: Call dp_client.bootstrap_session_id() when no session_id provided\n93:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n94:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestSessionBootstrap -v`\n95: \n96: - [ ] **T2.6**: Implement `_init_data_plane()` private method\n97:   - Purpose: Initialize AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with router_url, namespace, agent_name\n98:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n99:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestDataPlaneInit -v`\n100: \n101: - [ ] **T2.7**: Implement `__enter__()` context manager method\n102:   - Purpose: Return self for context manager usage\n103:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n104:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestContextManager -v`\n105: \n106: - [ ] **T2.8**: Implement `__exit__()` context manager method\n107:   - Purpose: Call close() on context exit (with or without exception)\n108:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n109:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestContextManager::test_context_manager_calls_close -v`\n110: \n111: - [ ] **T2.9**: Implement `invoke()` method with payload and optional timeout\n112:   - Purpose: Delegate to dp_client.invoke with session_id and payload\n113:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n114:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestInvoke -v`\n115: \n116: - [ ] **T2.10**: Implement `invoke()` session_id validation\n117:   - Purpose: Raise ValueError if session_id is None when invoke called\n118:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n119:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestInvoke::test_invoke_without_session -v`\n120: \n121: - [ ] **T2.11**: Implement `close()` method\n122:   - Purpose: Close data-plane HTTP session via dp_client.close()\n123:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n124:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestClose -v`\n125: \n126: ### Phase 3: Package Exports (ST-3)\n127: \n128: - [ ] **T3.1**: Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` with AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient export\n129:   - Purpose: Export AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient from clients package\n130:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n131:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient; print('OK')\"`\n132: \n133: - [ ] **T3.2**: Update `agentcube/__init__.py` with AgentRuntimeClient export\n134:   - Purpose: Export AgentRuntimeClient from top-level package\n135:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`\n136:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient; print('OK')\"`\n137: \n138: ### Phase 4: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Unit Tests (ST-4)\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T4.1**: Test AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient init with default timeout values\n141:   - Purpose: Verify default timeout 120s, connect_timeout 5.0s\n142:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n143:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestDataPlaneClientInit::test_init_default_timeout -v`\n144: \n145: - [ ] **T4.2**: Test AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient init with custom timeout\n146:   - Purpose: Verify custom timeout values are stored\n147:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n148:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestDataPlaneClientInit::test_init_custom_timeout -v`\n149: \n150: - [ ] **T4.3**: Test SESSION_HEADER constant value\n151:   - Purpose: Verify SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n152:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n153:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestSessionHeaderConstant -v`\n154: \n155: - [ ] **T4.4**: Test base_url construction with urljoin\n156:   - Purpose: Verify base_url built from router_url + namespace + agent_name\n157:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n158:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestBaseURLConstruction -v`\n159: \n160: - [ ] **T4.5**: Test connection pooling configuration\n161:   - Purpose: Verify HTTPAdapter mounted with pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10\n162:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n163:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestConnectionPooling -v`\n164: \n165: - [ ] **T4.6**: Test bootstrap_session_id success\n166:   - Purpose: Verify GET returns session_id from header\n167:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n168:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestBootstrapSessionID::test_bootstrap_success -v`\n169: \n170: - [ ] **T4.7**: Test bootstrap_session_id missing header raises ValueError\n171:   - Purpose: Verify ValueError raised when x-agentcube-session-id header absent\n172:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n173:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestBootstrapSessionID::test_bootstrap_missing_header -v`\n174: \n175: - [ ] **T4.8**: Test invoke with session_id and payload\n176:   - Purpose: Verify POST to base_url with json=payload and session header\n177:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n178:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestInvoke::test_invoke_with_session -v`\n179: \n180: - [ ] **T4.9**: Test invoke headers correctness\n181:   - Purpose: Verify both x-agentcube-session-id and Content-Type: application/json headers\n182:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n183:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestInvokeHeaders -v`\n184: \n185: - [ ] **T4.10**: Test invoke timeout override\n186:   - Purpose: Verify timeout=(connect_timeout, passed_timeout) when timeout argument provided\n187:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n188:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestInvokeTimeout::test_invoke_timeout_override -v`\n189: \n190: - [ ] **T4.11**: Test invoke timeout default fallback\n191:   - Purpose: Verify timeout=(connect_timeout, self.timeout) when timeout argument omitted\n192:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n193:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestInvokeTimeout::test_invoke_timeout_default -v`\n194: \n195: - [ ] **T4.12**: Test close method\n196:   - Purpose: Verify HTTP session closed\n197:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n198:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestClose -v`\n199: \n200: ### Phase 5: AgentRuntimeClient Unit Tests (ST-5)\n201: \n202: - [ ] **T5.1**: Test AgentRuntimeClient init with all params\n203:   - Purpose: Verify all init parameters stored correctly\n204:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n205:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestAgentRuntimeClientInit::test_init_all_params -v`\n206: \n207: - [ ] **T5.2**: Test Router URL required raises ValueError\n208:   - Purpose: Verify ValueError when router_url missing\n209:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n210:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestRouterURLRequired::test_router_url_required -v`\n211: \n212: - [ ] **T5.3**: Test Router URL from env var\n213:   - Purpose: Verify ROUTER_URL env var fallback\n214:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_